==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesh
<hw>Mesh</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>masc</ets>, <ets>max</ets>, <ets>m⟦ae⟧scre</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>maas</ets>, <ets>masche</ets>, OHG. <ets>masca</ets>, Icel.
<ets>m⟦oum⟧skvi</ets>; cf. Lith. <ets>mazgas</ets> a knot,
<ets>megsti</ets> to weave nets, to knot.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
opening or space inclosed by the threads of a net between knot and knot,
or the threads inclosing such a space; network; a net.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A golden <qex>mesh</qex> to entrap the hearts of men.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gearing)</fld> <def>The engagement of the teeth of
wheels, or of a wheel and rack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mesh stick</b></col>, <cd>a stick on which the mesh is
formed in netting.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mesh
<hw>Mesh</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Meshed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Meshing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To catch in a mesh.</def>
<rj><au>Surrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mesh
<hw>Mesh</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Gearing)</fld> <def>To engage with
each other, as the teeth of wheels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meshed</ent>⟦br⟧
